Title: [Project Spotlight] AARO: An Autonomous Approach to Federated Compute Efficiency

The Problem: As we move toward larger agentic AI workflows, the "Thermal Tax"—the massive energy cost of running high-depth reasoning locally—becomes a major bottleneck for sovereign, edge-based systems.

The Solution: I’ve been researching a modular approach called AARO (Autonomous Adaptive Resource Orchestrator). AARO acts as a governance layer that monitors real-time compute load and dynamically federates heavy reasoning tasks to remote compute nodes.

Key Metrics:

Local Baseline: 45.75W

Efficiency Achieved: 2.06 Tokens/Watt (Hybrid Equilibrium)

Architecture: Modular PowerShell-based orchestration (platform-agnostic).

Why it Matters: This isn't just about saving power; it's about enabling "Sovereign AI"—systems that understand their own metabolic limits and can sustain themselves in resource-constrained environments.

